section.title: Ethernet Interface Datapath Segments
section.p: There are three datapath segment provisioning options when configuring the Ethernet Subsystem for an Ethernet Rate.

li.p: Ethernet clients are terminated and their packet payloads are sent to the Interlaken interface.
Ethernet clients are terminated and their packet payloads are OTN mapped or the Ethernet client is OTN mapped transparently.
Ethernet clients are passed through the device transparently in re-timer mode.

section.p: The API g5_api_enet_prov() is used to configure the options above and their datapath segments are shown in the following figures. For full details on the parameters of the API g5_api_enet_prov() see the Provisioning and De-provisioning section of the ENET Subsystem.

Figure 1shows the datapath configured from the SERDES interface(A) through the ENET Subsystem to the edge of the ENET block(B) for Ethernet clients that are terminated to the Interlaken interface via the DCPB or Ethernet clients that are OTN mapped and pass through the ECPB to the MAPOTN block.

fig.title: Ethernet Datapath Segment Provisioning: Packet Termination or OTN Mapping

section.p: Figure 2 shows the datapath configured from the SERDES interface(A) back through the DSIS block(B) for Ethernet clients that transparently re-timed from SERDES Bank A to SERDES Bank B.

fig.title: Ethernet Datapath Segment Provisioning: Re-timer

section.title: FlexE Interface Group and Client Datapath Segment Provisioning
section.p: There are three FlexE operational modes supported by the device: FlexE PHY Terminated, FlexE OTN Aware/Unaware, and FlexE PHY Aware. Each mode has a unique provisioning procedure for FlexE interface groups and client datapath segments detailed in the following sub sections.

In FlexE PHY Terminated mode, FlexE clients from FlexE groups on physical 100GE ports are terminated to the Interlaken PIF interface or are mapped into OTN payloads. The provisioning sequence and APIs are shown below.

li.p: FlexE groups on physical 100GE ports have their configuration options defined with the g5_api_flexe_group_prov() API.
N x FlexE 100GE PHYs are added to the group with the g5_api_flexe_phy_add() API. N = 1 to 6.

Provisioning and activation of the FlexE group defined with steps 1 to 2 above is done with the g5_api_flexe_group_config() API. An error code will be returned if the API in steps 1 to 2 were not called in an atomic sequence or if insufficient PHY and (sub)group configuration information has been supplied.

FlexE clients inside the groups are provisioned with the g5_api_flexe_client_prov() API. FlexE clients are either terminated to the DCPB to be sent to the Interlaken PIF interface or are mapped to ODUk payloads via the ECPB.
The g5_api_flexe_calendar_update() API must be called to update the FlexE group calendar as the final step.

section.p: For full details on the parameters of the APIs above see the Provisioning and De-provisioning section of the ENET Subsystem.

FlexE group configuration, PHY add(s), group provisioning and group activation is shown in Figure 3 below. In this case the datapath is provisioned from the SERDES interface(A) through the FlexE block(B) in the ENET subsystem.

fig.title: FlexE Group Segment Provision: FlexE PHY/Group

section.p: FlexE client provisioning for clients that will be terminated to the Interlaken PIF interface is shown in Figure 4 below. In this case the datapath is provisioned from the FlexE Mux block (A) to the DCPB block(B).

fig.title: FlexE Client Datapath Segment Provisioning: Interlaken Packet Termination Traffic

section.p: FlexE client provisioning for clients that will be mapped to ODUks is shown in Figure 5 below. In this case the datapath is provisioned from the FlexE Mux block(A) through the ECPB block through the MAPOTN to the OCPB block(B).

fig.title: FlexE Client Datapath Segment Provisioning: OTN Mapped Traffic

section.p: In FlexE OTN Aware/Unaware mode, FlexE clients from FlexE groups from ODUCn payloads are terminated to the Interlaken PIF. The provisioning sequence and APIs are shown below.

li.p: FlexE group configuration options are defined with the g5_api_flexe_group_prov() API.
N x FlexE 100GE PHYs are added to the group with the g5_api_flexe_phy_add() API. N = 1 to 6. These PHYS are virtual as they are not associated to physical 100GE ports, rather to ODUCn payloads.
M x FlexE sub groups are added with the g5_api_flexe_subgroup_add(). M = 1 to 6 and M <= N.

Provisioning and activation of the FlexE group defined with steps 1 to 3 above is done with the g5_api_flexe_group_config() API. An error code will be returned if the API in steps 1 to 3 were not called in an atomic sequence or if insufficient PHY and (sub)group configuration information has been supplied.
FlexE clients are provisioned with the g5_api_flexe_client_prov() API. FlexE clients are terminated to the DCPB to be sent to the Interlaken PIF interface or are mapped to ODUk payloads via the ECPB.
The g5_api_flexe_calendar_update() API must be called to update the FlexE group calendar as the final step.

section.p: For full details on the parameters of the APIs above see the Provisioning and De-provisioning section of the ENET Subsystem.

FlexE group configuration, PHY add(s), sub group add(s), group provisioning and group activation is shown in Figure 6 below. In this case the datapath is provisioned from the OCPB block(A) to the FlexE block(B) in the ENET subsystem.

fig.title: FlexE Group Segment Provision: FlexE OTN Mapping

section.p: FlexE client provisioning is shown in Figure 7 below. In this case the datapath is provisioned from the FlexE Mux block (A) to the DCPB block(B).

fig.title: FlexE Client Datapath Segment Provisioning: Interlaken Packet Termination Traffic

section.p: In FlexE PHY Aware mode, FlexE groups and subgroups from physical 100GE ports are transparently mapped to ODUk and ODUCn payloads. The provisioning sequence and APIs are shown below.

li.p: FlexE group configuration options are defined with the g5_api_flexe_group_prov() API.
N x FlexE 100GE PHYs are added to the group with the g5_api_flexe_phy_add() API. N = 1 to 6.
M x FlexE sub groups are added with the g5_api_flexe_subgroup_add(). M = 1 to 6 and M <= N.

Provisioning and activation of the FlexE group defined with steps 1 to 3 above is done with the g5_api_flexe_group_config() API. An error code will be returned if the API in steps 1 to 3 were not called in an atomic sequence or if insufficient PHY and (sub)group configuration information has been supplied.

section.p: For full details on the parameters of the APIs above see the Provisioning and De-provisioning section of the ENET Subsystem.

The FlexE group provision is shown in Figure 8 below. In this case the datapath is provisioned from the SERDES interface(A) to the FlexE block(B) in the ENET subsystem. Mapping of the FlexE Aware group is done with the g5_api_client_map_cfg() API and described below.

fig.title: FlexE Group Segment Provision: Serdes Interface to FlexE Block

section.title: Client Mapping Datapath Segment Provisioning
section.p: The g5_api_client_map_cfg() API provides the following mapping options for Ethernet Subsystem or Interlaken sourced traffic.

li.p: Transparent Ethernet traffic from the Ethernet Subsystem that is GMP/BMP OTN mapped.
Terminated Ethernet traffic from the Ethernet Subsystem that is GMP/BMP/GFP OTN mapped.
Ethernet traffic that is terminated at the Interlaken interface and is GMP/BMP/GFP OTN mapped.
Packet traffic that is terminated at the Interlaken interface and is GFP OTN mapped.
FlexE clients that are terminated and their packet payloads are GFP OTN mapped.
FlexE clients that are IMP OTN mapped transparently.

section.p: For full details on the parameters of the g5_api_client_map_cfg() API see the Provisioning and De-provisioning section of the MAPOTN Subsystem.

Figure 9 shows the transparent Ethernet traffic sourced from the ENET block(A) and sent through the ECPB to the MAPOTN subsystem to be GMP/BMP OTN mapped and then the resulting ODUk is sent to the OCPB block(B) of the COREOTN subsystem. For transparent Ethernet segment provisioning, the matching ENET channel from the g5_api_enet_prov() API is used for the chnl_id of g5_api_client_map_cfg() API.

fig.title: Client Mapping Datapath Segment Provisioning: Transparent Ethernet Traffic OTN Mapped

section.p: Figure 10 shows the terminated Ethernet traffic sourced from the ENET block(A) and sent through the ECPB to the MAPOTN subsystem to be OTN mapped and then the resulting ODUk is sent to the OCPB block(B) of the COREOTN subsystem.

fig.title: Client Mapping Datapath Segment Provisioning: Terminated Ethernet Traffic OTN Mapped

section.p: Figure 11 shows the terminated Ethernet traffic from an Interlaken channel from the DCPB block(A) to the Ethernet Subsystem and then through the ECPB block and sent to the MAPOTN subsystem to be GMP/BMP/GFP OTN mapped and then the resulting ODUk is sent to the OCPB block(B) of the COREOTN subsystem.

fig.title: Client Mapping Datapath Segment Provisioning: Interlaken Sourced Ethernet Traffic OTN Mapped

section.p: Figure 12 shows the terminated packet traffic from an Interlaken channel from the DCPB block(A) to the MAPOTN subsystem to be GFP OTN mapped and then the resulting ODUk is sent to the OCPB block(B) of the COREOTN subsystem.

fig.title: Client Mapping Datapath Segment Provisioning: Packet Traffic OTN Mapped

section.p: Figure 13 shows the datapath configured from the FlexE block(A) through the Ethernet Subsystem to the ECPB(B) for FlexE clients that are terminated and their packet payloads are OTN mapped or for FlexE Aware groups that are transparently OTN mapped.

fig.title: FlexE Datapath Segment Provisioning: FlexE OTN Mapped Traffic

section.title: Interlaken Channel Datapath Segment Provisioning
section.p: Interlaken interface channel datapath segment provisioning is performed by initializing the flow control calendars with the g5_api_ilkn_fc_set() API and provisioning the channel with either the g5_api_ilkn_pkt_prov() API or g5_api_ilkn_cbr_prov() API.

The API, g5_api_ilkn_pkt_prov(), provisions the COPI subsystem and the Interlaken Interface's channel for packet terminated datapath segments. Figure 14 shows the datapath segment from the DCPB(A) through the COPI Subsystem to the Interlaken interface(B).

fig.title: Interlaken Datapath Segment Provisioning: DCPB to Interlaken Interface

section.p: The API, g5_api_ilkn_cbr_prov(), provisions the SAR block, DCPB block, COPI subsystem and the Interlaken Interface's channel for CBR datapath segments. Figure 15 shows the datapath segment provisioning from the OCPB block(A) of the COREOTN through the SAR block, then through the DCPB block and through the COPI subsystem to the Interlaken interface(B).

fig.title: Interlaken Datapath Segment Provisioning: OCPB to Interlaken Interface

section.p: In n x 200G Interlaken interface mode three additional API are required to select from which one of the up to three Interlaken interfaces the channel data is sent to the DCPB block. The API are as follows:

li.p: g5_api_ilkn_chnl_id_bcw_set() - used in n x 200G ILKN mode to set Fabric Egress BCW channel ID for a common DPI channel to DCPB. Valid interface are the G5_ILKN_INTF_1 and G5_ILKN_INTF_2. G5_ILKN_INTF_0 is set as part of g5_api_ilkn_cbr_prov() or g5_api_ilkn_pkt_prov() API.
g5_api_ilkn_fabric_egress_select() - selects which fabric egress n x ILKN interface channel to be the active interface that DCPB receives data from.
g5_api_ilkn_fabric_ingress_chnl_activate() - selects an ILKN interface that the provisioned channel id is to transfer DCPB data to.

section.title: OTN Port Datapath Segment Provisioning
section.p: There are three options for provisioning OTN port datapath segments using the g5_api_otn_prov() API.

li.p: OTN interfaces via the Line OTN subsystem that are channelized or unchannelized.
OTN interfaces via the System OTN subsystem that are unchannelized.

section.p: For full details on the parameters of the API g5_api_otn_prov() see the Provisioning and De-provisioning section of the LINEOTN Subsystem.

Figure 16 shows the datapath segment provisioning for an OTN port from the SERDES interface passing through the LINEOTN subsystem to the COREOTN subsystem. When and OTUk is initially provisioned the datapath segment will connect the High Order ODUk of the OTUk from the SERDES interface(A) to the OCPB block(C), bypassing the High Order and Low Order Multiplexer blocks. If a High Order Multiplexer datapath segment provisioning API is called to configure the High Order Multiplexer then the High Order ODUk from the OTUk on the line will terminate at the first ODUk framer(B) in the COREOTN.

fig.title: OTN Port Datapath Segment Provisioning: LINEOTN Channelized or Unchannelized OTU4 Traffic

section.p: Figure 17 shows the datapath segment provisioning for an OTN port passing through the SYSOTN subsystem to the COREOTN subsystem. The datapath segment will connect the High Order ODUk of the OTUk from the SERDES interface(A) to the OCPB block(B).

fig.title: OTN Port Datapath Segment Provisioning: SYSOTN Unchannelized OTU4 Traffic

section.title: OTUCn and FlexO Interface Group Datapath Segment Provisioning
section.p: OTUCn and FlexO Groups are provisioned following the API sequence below.

li.p: OTUCn or FlexO group configuration options are defined with the g5_api_otucn_group_prov() API.
N x OTUCn or FlexO PHYs are added to the group with the g5_api_otucn_port_add() API. N = 1 to 6.
Provisioning and activation of the OTUCn or FlexO group defined with steps 1 and 2 above is done with the g5_api_otucn_group_config() API.

section.p: For full details on the parameters of the APIs above see the Provisioning and De-provisioning section of the LINEOTN Subsystem.

The OTUCn or FlexO group provision for the LINEOTN is shown in Figure 18 below. In this case the datapath is provisioned from the SERDES interface(A) through the OTU framer block(B) in the LINEOTN subsystem.

fig.title: OTUCn or FlexO Group Segment Provision: LINEOTN Channelized or Unchannelized OTUCn or FlexO Traffic

section.p: The OTUCn or FlexO group provision for the SYSOTN is shown in Figure 19 below. In this case the datapath is provisioned from the SERDES interface(A) through the OTU framer block(B) in the SYSOTN subsystem.

fig.title: OTUCn or FlexO Group Segment Provision: SYSOTN Unchannelized OTUCn or FlexO Traffic

section.title: High Order ODUCn / ODUjk and Low Order ODUjk Mux Datapath Segment Provisioning
section.p: High Order (HO) ODUCn / ODUjk and Low Order (LO) ODUjk multiplexing datapath segments are provisioned with the API g5_api_odu_mux_cfg(). This API is called after the OTUk or OTUCn port has been provisioned or after the High Order multiplexing datapath segment has been provisioned. When the API g5_api_odu_mux_cfg() is configured as the second stage of ODUjk multiplexing, the LINEOTN interface may have up to 500G of provisioned SERDES ports. If 600G of SERDES ports are provisioned then the second stage of ODUjk multiplexing is unavailable.

Figure 20 shows the datapath segment provisioning for High Order ODUCn or ODUjk multiplexing. Initially the segment is provisioned from the High Order ODUC / ODU framer(A) to the OCPB block(C) and will remain for ODUCn multiplexing or 1-stage ODUjk multiplexing mode. However, if a LO ODUjk multiplexing datapath segment is provisioned following the High Order segment provisioning, the datapath segment for the High Order ODUC / ODUk is from the High Order ODUC / ODU framer(A) to the input of the LO Mux block(B).

fig.title: HO ODUC / ODUk Mux Datapath Segment Provisioning: HO ODUC or ODUjk Multiplexing

section.p: Figure 21 shows the datapath segment provisioning for LO ODUjk multiplexing. The segment is provisioned from the LO ODU framer(A) to the OCPB block(B).

fig.title: LO ODUk Mux Datapath Segment Provisioning: LO ODUjk Multiplexing

section.title: Central Packet Buffer Switch Segment Provisioning
section.p: The ODUk Central Packet Buffer (OCPB) and packet Data Central Packet Buffer (DCPB) are provisioned with the g5_api_switch_connect() API. The Ethernet Packet Central Packet Buffer (ECPB) is provisioned with the g5_api_client_map_cfg() API and will not be discussed in this section.

This function connects a destination channel to its data source in a unidirectional manner at OCPB or DCPB switches. The switch link is determined from the source and destination channel IDs as specified by the parameters src_chnl_id and dst_chnl_id. A loopback is formed when src_chnl_id = dst_chnl_id. See the loopback section of this document for additional information. For a bi-directional path the g5_api_switch_connect() API is called twice with the source and destinations channel IDs swapped for the two calls.
OCPB bi-directional datapath segments are shown in Figure 22 below. Valid paths are from LINEOTN/COREOTN to MAPOTN, SAR or SYSOTN.

fig.title: OCPB Bi-Directional Datapath Segments

section.p: OCPB bi-directional datapath segments with a bi-cast are shown in Figure 23 below. The paths shown below are LINEOTN bi-cast to both the MAPOTN and SAR, LINEOTN bi-cast to the SYSOTN and SAR and MAPOTN bi-cast to the LINEOTN and SYSOTN.

fig.title: OCPB Bi-Directional Datapath Segments with Bi-cast

section.p: The DCPB bi-directional datapath segments of ENET to PIF is shown in Figure 24 below. ENET to MAPOTN, MAPOTN to PIF and SAR to PIF are all provisioned within the g5_api_client_map_cfg() and g5_api_ilkn_cbr_prov() APIs.

fig.title: DCPB Bi-Directional Datapath Segments
